These values are based on point intersections of live vegetation with a sighting tube at 25 points on eight 12.6 m transects through the 0.05-ha plot. Readings were taken in the center of each habitat sampling plot and at 4 m, 8 m, and 12 m on each of the eight transects within the plot. The transects are at 45 degree increments with one transect to the north. The herb layer is vegetation < 0.5 m tall, the shrub layer is vegetation > 0.5-2.0 m tall, while the tree layer vegetation is > 2.0 m tall.</dct:description>
